Description: # Vali
        ## Easy type checking
        ```python
        from vali import validate
        
        foo = 'string'
        bar = 16
        baz = ('string', 3)
        
        results = validate(dict(
            'str': foo,
            'int': bar,
            'tuple': baz
        ))
        
        if not results:
            print("Ahhh")
        ```
        
        It can also throw an exception if you want:
        ```python
        from vali import validate
        
        foo = 'string'
        bar = 16
        baz = ('string', 3)
        
        results = validate(dict(
            'tuple': foo, # This will throw an exception
            'int': bar,
            'tuple': baz
        ), return_type='Exception')
        ```
        
